    <h2>Problems</h2>
    <p>
      There are some typical problems that led to the development of calculus.
      <ul>
        <li>
          Finding the instantaneous velocity of a particle moving along a know
          path.
        </li>
        <li>Finding the tangent line to a curve at a given point.</li>
        <li>Finding maxima and minima of a quantity.</li>
        <li>Finding a line with the same lenght of a given curve.</li>
        <li>
          Finding the measure (area or volume) of a figure (in plane or space).
        </li>
      </ul>
    </p>

